article.headline: Gonzaga 59, Oklahoma 41
article.story: SPOKANE, Wash. -- Steven Gray scored 18 points as hot-shooting Gonzaga beat Oklahoma 83-69 on Thursday night. Elias Harris added 15 points and Bol Kong 14 as Gonzaga (10-3) had five players in double figures. The Bulldogs shot 50 percent and made 11 3-pointers, many on wide-open looks. Willie Warren led Oklahoma (8-5) with 19 points. The Sooners have lost two straight. Oklahoma's Tiny Gallon got the New Year's Eve festivities off to an early start when he shattered a backboard in the second half.
